At first we thought it was a Tawny Pipit, but it appears to be Tree Sparrow. We didn`t see the flying by bird.

**Comments:** Flock of at least 20 birds. The same individuals as in XC585842. Insects can be heared in the background.

**Recording modofications:** No edits. Recorded using ZOOM H1n. 

**Habitat:** Reed beds at small water reservoir (partly dry). 

**Weather and other conditions:** Windy.
